ed a pair of funds including the third in its series of main funds carlyleriverstone global energy and power iii which raised  billion of capital the two firms also raised their first renewable energy focused fund carlyleriverstone renewable energy infrastructure fund i with  million history of private equity and venture capital early history origins of modern private equity the s leveraged buyout boom the s leveraged buyout and the venture capital bubble the s dotcom bubble to the credit crunch v t e also in  riverstone was a member of a consortium of private equity firms including goldman sachs capital partners and carlyle group that completed the  billion including assumed debt acquisition of kinder morgan one of the largest pipeline operators in the us the buyout was backed by richard kinder a former president of enron in  riverstone and carlyle raised  billion for their fourth main energy fund riverstonecarlyle global power  energy fund iv additionally in  the firms raised a  billion riverstonecarlyle renewable energy infrastructure fund ii as a successor to the  million fund raised in  to focus on renewable energy investments operationsedit in  riverstone and carlyle have six main funds focused on buyouts in energy with approximately  billion of raised capital controversiesedit in  the new york attorney general andrew cuomo ordered riverstone holdings llc to pay  million in restitution after riverstone holdings employed fixers to get them business from pension funds controlled by corrupt state officials greenenvironmental initiativesedit in march  riverstonecarlyle made an investment in enviva partners lp enviva is one of the largest suppliers of sustainably sourced wood pellets and other processed woody biomass in the world these products are used by industrial customers seeking to decrease their dependence on foreign fuel and their carbon footprint the aes corporation and riverstone holdings llc announced on march  that they have committed up to  billion as a part of a new joint venture to develop a global platform of utilityscale solar photovoltaic projects together these firms have provided  million of capital over five years to invest in pv solar projects around the world this jointly owned entity is known as aes solar they seek to be the leading global developer and operator of utilityscale solar installations that will be connected to power grids that supply and businesses these installations consist of land based solar pv panels that capture sunlight and convert it to electricity in order to feed the power grid referencesedit  p f lapeyre jrand miss hodgesto wed in march nytimescom  retrieved    did goldman goose oil forbes april    archived copy archived from the original on july   retrieved october     mouawad jad kinder morgan agrees to an improved buyout offer led by its chairman the new york times august    centopani paul  buyouts archive  pe hub buyoutsnewscom retrieved    archived copy archived from the original on september   retrieved august     riverstone raises  billion for energy fund reuters  june  retrieved  august    extol energy formed to pursue power investment opportunities with riverstone holdings  april  retrieved  august    pay to play scandal in ny nabs another investment firm abc  june  retrieved  august    green initiative task force pdf retrieved  june    riverstone aes partner for b solar projects venture reliableplantcom retrieved   other sourcesedit williams to sell control of energy unit for  billion the new york times tuesday april   carlyle riverstone power up with b for two funds firms add more public pensions to lp base the new york times private equity week april   lord brownes renewable career business week october   retrieved from httpsenwikipediaorgwindexphptitleriverstoneholdingsoldid categories private equity firms of the united statesenergy companies of the united statespower companies of the united stateshidden categories pages using deprecated image syntax navigation menu